[
    "Based on the provided documentation, here is how inheritance of multisite descriptions is handled for B2 and B3 blocks and how it can be overridden.",
    "Multisite data are inherited automatically by all subordinate B2 and B3 blocks from their parent B1 block.",
    "When you open the Multisite Form for a B2 or B3 block, the data from its parent B1 block are automatically populated in the form's tabular list.",
    "To override this automatic inheritance, you can use the "Disinherit" button.",
    "In the Multisite Form for the specific B2 or B3 block, locate the "Disinherit" button on the right side of the tabular list.",
    "Press the "Disinherit" button.",
    "The fields in the tabular list are unlocked and become available for manual input.",
    "The "Disinherit" button changes to a "Reinherit" button.",
    "You can now enter new, specific multisite data for that particular B2 or B3 block.",
    "If you wish to revert to the inherited data from the parent B1 block, you can do so by pressing the "Reinherit" button.",
    "This will undo the disinherit operation and the form will once again display the inherited data."
] 

