Statements:
[
    "Based on the provided documentation, the requirements for assigning a formula to an application data info in the Calculation Worksheet are as follows:",
    "The application data info must be a "calculated application data info".",
    "This means its input mode must have been set to IO during the system configuration phase.",
    "The desired formula must have been defined previously via the SDM system.",
    "The application data info can be selected from the Application Data Info Tabular List of the Application Data Info Worksheet.",
    "The application data info can be selected from the pop-list Info Name in the Result Block of the Calculation Worksheet.",
    "The Info Name pop-list only contains calculated application data infos (those with input mode IO).",
    "Select the Calculation Worksheet by clicking the radio button Calculation in the worksheet selection group of the Detail Block.",
    "Enter the name of the desired formula into the text field of the attribute Formula.",
    "Alternatively, double-click the Formula text field to open a list of values and select the formula from there.",
    "The data type of the formula's result must match the application data type of the selected application data info.",
    "For example, if the application data info is a binary value, the formula's result must also be a binary value.",
    "The list of values for the Formula attribute will only show formulae whose result data type corresponds to the data type of the selected application data info.",
    "Any attempt to assign a formula with a non-matching data type will be rejected.",
    "The formula assignment can only be modified if no operands have been specified (i.e., the Operands Tabular List is empty).",
    "Once a formula is selected and at least one operand is defined, the Formula field becomes protected and the assignment cannot be changed."
] 

