Statements:
[
    "Based on the provided documentation, a Technological Address (TA) consists of five parts that form a hierarchical structure to uniquely identify information in the system.",
    "The five parts of a Technological Address (TA) are:",
    "B1-Name represents the highest level, typically used to identify substations and lines in the system.",
    "B2-Name represents the next level, defining the various voltage levels within each station or line.",
    "B3-Name represents the level containing switchbays and network components (e.g., name, block type, topology type).",
    "Element-Name represents the elements contained within the switchbays and network components.",
    "The element type determines the associated data units.",
    "Info-Name represents the individual technological data units (infos) contained within each element.",
    "This 5-level hierarchy (B1/B2/B3/Element/Info) provides a unique identification for data records in the database."
] 

